  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into chips</p><p>Drain your <strong>beetroot</strong> in a colander over the sink</p><p>Cut <strong>half</strong> the <strong>drained beetroot</strong> into chips (you'll use the rest later!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1675772531135-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1675772531135-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1675772531135-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1675772531135-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1675772531135-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato & beetroot chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until crisp and golden</p><p>Whilst the chips are in the oven, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic </strong>and grate the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>beetroot</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1675772539103-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1675772539103-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1675772539103-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1675772539103-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1675772539103-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>chilli</strong> <strong>flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>cumin</strong> <strong>seeds</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant, then add the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>beetroot</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>white</strong> <strong>wine</strong> <strong>vinegar </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml]</span> <strong>water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 7-8 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>cumin</strong> <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>beetroot</strong> <strong>relish</strong></p><p>Once thickened, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
